    "image_with_text_FAfVaW": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_tfc8jA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q: </strong>Outside of coffee and matcha, what little things in life bring you joy and help you slow down?</p><p><strong>A: </strong>Most of our joys are rooted in family, genuine connections and travel. Our family is a big part of our lives, so even simple moments like cooking together or catching up after a long day help us slow down. We also enjoy traveling. Exploring new places helps us reset, stay curious, and appreciate the small things.</p><p><strong>Q</strong>: How do you see Idle Hours evolving in the future? Any exciting projects coming up?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> To be very honest, we’re not planners. We live in the moment and do what feels exciting and right with the best intentions. This is why Idle Hours is almost 6 months in with so many pop-ups with local businesses in the city, and we can’t believe it. Looking ahead, our goal is to keep building with that same spirit—creating unique, fun flavors and giving people a welcoming space to gather, slow down, and connect with like-minded souls. We’re excited to keep exploring collaborations, seasonal drinks, and little moments that make everyday life a bit more joyful. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
